Multi-tenancy in Wazuh means allowing multiple independent users, teams, or organizations to use the same Wazuh environment while keeping their data separated.

With multi-tenancy:

Admin → Has all the access to the data coming for server A and Server B
User 1 → sees only their data for server A
User 2 → sees only their datanfor server B

They cannot see each other's data.

